## General Guidelines

1. **Always use lazy finders** when possible for better performance
2. **Use `@webpack/common`** for Discord components and stores
3. **Wait for modules** instead of assuming they're loaded
4. **Use filters** instead of custom filter functions
5. **Clean up subscriptions** - Unsubscribe from Flux events
6. **Type safety** - All webpack utilities are typed
7. **Error handling** - Handle cases where modules might not be found

---

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **DON'T**: Directly access webpack internals
```typescript
// BAD
const module = window.webpackChunkdiscord_app[0][1](12345);

// GOOD
import { findByProps } from "@webpack";
const module = findByProps("getUser");
```

❌ **DON'T**: Use non-lazy finders in hot paths
```typescript
// BAD (in render function)
function Component() {
    const UserStore = findByProps("getUser"); // Runs every render
    return <div>{UserStore.getCurrentUser().username}</div>;
}

// GOOD
import { findByPropsLazy } from "@webpack";
const UserStore = findByPropsLazy("getUser");

function Component() {
    const user = UserStore.getCurrentUser();
    return <div>{user.username}</div>;
}
```

❌ **DON'T**: Find stores manually
```typescript
// BAD
const UserStore = findByProps("getUser", "getCurrentUser");

// GOOD
import { UserStore } from "@webpack/common";
const user = UserStore.getCurrentUser();
```

❌ **DON'T**: Hardcode module IDs
```typescript
// BAD
const module = wreq(12345);

// GOOD
import { findByProps } from "@webpack";
const module = findByProps("something");
```

❌ **DON'T**: Poll for modules
```typescript
// BAD
let module;
const interval = setInterval(() => {
    module = findByProps("getUser");
    if (module) clearInterval(interval);
}, 100);

// GOOD
import { waitFor } from "@webpack";
waitFor(["getUser"], (UserStore) => {
    // Module is available
});
```

❌ **DON'T**: Forget to unsubscribe
```typescript
// BAD
FluxDispatcher.subscribe("MESSAGE_CREATE", handler);
// Never unsubscribes

// GOOD
import { FluxDispatcher } from "@webpack/common";

// In component
useEffect(() => {
    FluxDispatcher.subscribe("MESSAGE_CREATE", handler);
    return () => FluxDispatcher.unsubscribe("MESSAGE_CREATE", handler);
}, []);
```

